~~ Image Divs ~~

topPostImageDiv => holds image element for top post
	- should be bigger than other images
	- size is dictated by container tho so this could be same for all of the posts
css:
.topPostImageDiv {
  height: 0;
  padding-bottom: 56.25%;
  overflow: hidden;
  margin: auto;
}

next3PostImageDiv => holds image for next 3 post images
css:
.next3PostImageDiv {
  height: 0;
  padding-bottom: 56.25%;
  overflow: hidden;
}

postImageDiv => holds image for regular posts
	- size should be set here because regular posts have following text rather than below text
css:
.postImageDiv{
  width: 20vw;
  display: block;
  height: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
  padding-bottom: 56.25%;
}

~~ Images ~~

topPostImage => Image for top post
css:
.topPostImage {
  width:100%;
  max-width: 100%;
}

next3PostImage => Image for a next 3 post
css:
.next3PostImage {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 100%;
}

postImage => Image for a regular post
css:
.postImage {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 100%;
}

~~ new image div class heirarchy ~~

.topPostImageDiv {
  height: 0;
  padding-bottom: 56.25%;
  overflow: hidden;
}
.next3PostImageDiv {
  height: 0;
  padding-bottom: 56.25%;
  overflow: hidden;
}
.postImageDiv{
  width: 20vw;
  display: block;
  height: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
  padding-bottom: 56.25%;
}

~~~~~~~~~~~

.postImageDiv {
    height: 0;
    padding-bottom: 56.25%;
    overflow: hidden;
}

.postImageDiv.regularImageDiv {
    width: 20vw;
}

~~ new image class ~~

.postImage {
    width:100%;
    max-width: 100%;
}

~~~~~~~~~~~~